Huge speedups in real-time rendering and video playback.

++ How SIMD Fits These Workloads
One instruction performs the same operation on multiple data elements simultaneously.
So instead of this:
for each pixel i:
    output[i] = (A[i] + B[i]) / 2
SIMD does this:
load vector of 8 pixels from A
load vector of 8 pixels from B
add vectors â†’ divide by 2
store vector result
âž¡ One instruction processes 8 pixels in one go (in a 128-bit SIMD register).
This is why SIMD can give 8Ã— or 16Ã— throughput improvement with almost the same control logic.

ðŸš€ SIMD Advantage
	â€¢	SIMD performs multiple MACs per cycle.
	â€¢	Vector ALUs handle several samples simultaneously.
	â€¢	Reduces instruction overhead (one instruction for multiple operations).

EXAMPLE: ARM NEON, Intel AVX / AVX2, Qualcomm Hexagon DSP, TI C6000 DSP
